theorem Topology.closure_eq_closure_interior_closure_of_P2
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P2 A → closure A = closure (interior (closure A)) := by
  intro hP2
  -- From `P2` we already have `closure A = closure (interior A)`.
  have h₁ : closure A = closure (interior A) :=
    Topology.closure_eq_closure_interior_of_P2 (A := A) hP2
  -- Prove the desired equality by double inclusion.
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · -- First inclusion: `closure A ⊆ closure (interior (closure A))`.
    have : closure (interior A) ⊆ closure (interior (closure A)) := by
      -- Use monotonicity of `closure` applied to
      -- `interior A ⊆ interior (closure A)`.
      have hsubset : interior A ⊆ interior (closure A) :=
        interior_subset_interior_closure (A := A)
      exact closure_mono hsubset
    simpa [h₁] using this
  · -- Second inclusion: `closure (interior (closure A)) ⊆ closure A`.
    have hsubset : interior (closure A) ⊆ closure A := interior_subset
    exact closure_mono hsubset

replace theorem P2_implies_P3 {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P2 A → Topology.P3 A := by
  intro hA
  dsimp [Topology.P2, Topology.P3] at hA ⊢
  -- We strengthen the intermediate inclusion step by making the use of `interior_subset`
  -- explicit, ensuring types align without relying on further rewriting.
  have hsubset : interior (closure (interior A)) ⊆ interior (closure A) := by
    -- First, upgrade `closure (interior A)` to `closure A`.
    have hclosure : closure (interior A) ⊆ closure A := by
      -- This follows from the monotonicity of `closure` applied to
      -- `interior_subset : interior A ⊆ A`.
      have hinner : interior A ⊆ (A : Set X) := interior_subset
      exact closure_mono hinner
    -- Then apply monotonicity of `interior`.
    exact interior_mono hclosure
  exact Set.Subset.trans hA hsubset

theorem Topology.interior_closure_subset_interior_closure_union_right
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    interior (closure B) ⊆ interior (closure (A ∪ B)) := by
  intro x hx
  -- `closure B` is contained in `closure (A ∪ B)`.
  have hsubset : closure B ⊆ closure (A ∪ B) := by
    apply closure_mono
    exact Set.subset_union_right
  -- Monotonicity of `interior` gives the desired inclusion.
  exact (interior_mono hsubset) hx
